22/03/2007
NEW YORK, United States -- Issues related to Kosovo, Cyprus and the name dispute between Greece and Macedonia dominated talks between Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis and UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon in New York on Wednesday (March 21st). Local media reports in Athens say that the new UN special mediator for the bilateral name dispute, US diplomat B. Lynn Pascoe, also attended the talks. He recently replaced Matthew Nimmitz. On Thursday, Bakoyannis is meeting with senior officials in Washington. (Kathimerini, Vecer - 22/03/07; ANA-MPA, ERT - 21/03/07)
